    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-02-10T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-02-10T11:00:00-05:00" n="38"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/3827: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-10T16:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 10, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>668. I have sent the following telegram to American Embassy, Archangel, in reply
                    to their February 4th, 4 p.m.:<note n="48" xml:id="d38fn48">A duplicate of the
                        telegram from Archangel to the Acting Secretary of State, no. 829, Feb. 4,
                            <ref target="#pg_42">p. 42</ref>.</note>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“As I feel that the decision which you communicated to the Mission in
                            your telegram number 31, February 4th, 4 p.m.,<note n="48"
                                xml:id="d38fn51">A duplicate of the telegram from Archangel to the
                                Acting Secretary of State, no. 829, Feb. 4, <ref target="#pg_42">p.
                                    42</ref>.</note> was possibly reached under a mistaken idea of
                            the scope and purposes of the decision of the Government of the United
                            States and the Allies in regard to the proposed meeting at Princes
                            Island, I desire to state that it is not the intention of the American
                            Government in agreeing to this meeting to barter in matters of principle
                            with the Bolshevist Government. The purpose of the meeting is rather
                            that of investigation in order that this Government may be in a position
                            intelligently to direct its future policy in regard to all factions in
                            Russia.</p>
                        <p>I appreciate the value of the work which you have done and I hope you may
                            find it possible to continue in this work as heretofore.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Subsequently I have noted your 480 to Archangel<note n="49" xml:id="d38fn49"
                        >Quoted in telegram to the Commission to Negotiate Peace, no. 620, Feb. 7,
                            <ref target="#pg_46">p. 46</ref>.</note> and <persName corresp="#p_PDC1"
                        >Poole</persName>’s report of 844 [<hi rend="italic">reply, 842</hi>].<note
                        n="50" xml:id="d38fn50">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
